body:
### Description

The following SystemVerilog code demonstrates a scenario where polymorphism is used to handle cross-module references (XMR) for dynamically accessing generated blocks. This approach works in simulators like VCS and Xcelium but fails in Verilator during the build phase.

### Example Code

```systemverilog
module Child;
  int value;
endmodule

module Parent;
  for (genvar i = 0; i < 10; i++) begin : gen_child
    Child child ();
  end
endmodule

module Testbench;
  Parent parent ();

  virtual class ChildAgentBase;
    pure virtual task preload(int value);
  endclass

  ChildAgentBase child_agents[10];

  for (genvar i = 0; i < 10; i++) begin
    class ChildAgent extends ChildAgentBase;
      task automatic preload(int value);
        parent.gen_child[i].child.value = value;
      endtask
    endclass

    ChildAgent agent = new();
    initial child_agents[i] = agent;
  end

  task automatic preload_children;
    for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) begin
      child_agents[i].preload(i);
    end
  endtask

  initial begin
    #1;  // Ensure all class instances are initialized
    preload_children();
    $display("%0d", parent.gen_child[3].child.value);
    $display("%0d", parent.gen_child[8].child.value);
  end

endmodule
```

### Verilator Command and Output

Command:

```bash
verilator test.sv --cc --exe --binary --main
```

Output:

```
%Error: test.sv:39:5: Duplicate declaration of CLASS 'ChildAgent': 'ChildAgent'
                    : ... note: In instance 'Testbench'
   39 |     class ChildAgent extends ChildAgentBase;
      |     ^~~~~
        test.sv:39:5: ... Location of original declaration
   39 |     class ChildAgent extends ChildAgentBase;
      |     ^~~~~
%Error: test.sv:39:5: Class 'ChildAgent' extends 'ChildAgentBase' but is missing implementation for 'preload' (IEEE 1800-2023 8.26)
                    : ... note: In instance 'Testbench'
   39 |     class ChildAgent extends ChildAgentBase;
      |     ^~~~~
        test.sv:33:23: ... Location of interface class's function
   33 |     pure virtual task preload(int value);
      |                       ^~~~~~~
%Error: Exiting due to 2 error(s)
```

### Expected Behavior

The code should compile and execute correctly, as it does with other simulators (VCS and Xcelium). This implementation relies on polymorphism to manage XMRs in generated blocks, which seems to be the only approach for such cases in SystemVerilog.

### Additional Information

- **Verilator version**: 5.031 devel rev v5.030-138-g965631152 (latest master branch)
- **Operating system**: WSL Ubuntu 24.04
- **Tested simulators**: VCS and Xcelium (code works as expected)

### Notes

A common instinctive approach, shown below, is incorrect because runtime variables cannot be used in XMR paths. This limitation necessitates a more complex solution, as described earlier.

```systemverilog
module Testbench;
  Parent parent ();

  task automatic preload_children;
    for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) begin
      parent.gen_child[i].child.value = i;  // Error: runtime variable `i` in XMR
    end
  endtask

  initial begin
    preload_children();
  end
endmodule
```

The example code described in this report is inspired by [a post on Verification Academy](https://verificationacademy.com/forums/t/accessing-task-of-generate-block-using-hierarchy-path/28872).

Thank you for your continued work on Verilator! Let me know if further clarification or assistance is needed.
